t      <h1>Computer Science > Computation and Language</h1>\n117\t    </div>\n118\t\n119\t    <div class=\"header-breadcrumbs-mobile\">\n120\t      <strong>arXiv:2607.04814v1</strong> (cs)\n121\t    </div>\n122\t<link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"/static/base/1.0.1/css/abs.css\">\n123\t<div id=\"content-inner\">\n124\t  <div id=\"abs\">\n125\t    <div class=\"dateline\">\n126\t  [Submitted on 6 Jul 2026]</div>\n127\t    <h1 class=\"title mathjax\"><span class=\"descriptor\">Title:</span>Evaluating the Effect of Linguistic Relatedness on Cross-Lingual Transfer in Large Multilingual Automatic Speech Recognition</h1>\n128\t    <div class=\"authors\"><span class=\"descriptor\">Authors:</span><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Florian,+A\" rel=\"nofollow\">Andrei Florian</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Amol,+C+J\" rel=\"nofollow\">Cynthia Jayne Amol</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Ombaba,+H+K\" rel=\"nofollow\">Hope Kerubo Ombaba</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Cui,+X\" rel=\"nofollow\">Xiaoyu Cui</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Mwau,+B\" rel=\"nofollow\">Boniface Mwau</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Kamau,+B+M\" rel=\"nofollow\">Biatus Maina Kamau</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Wanzare,+L+D+A\" rel=\"nofollow\">Lilian Diana Awuor Wanzare</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Fellbaum,+C\" rel=\"nofollow\">Christiane Fellbaum</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Buzaaba,+H\" rel=\"nofollow\">Happy Buzaaba</a></div>            <div id=\"download-button-info\" hidden>View a PDF of the paper titled Evaluating the Effect of Linguistic Relatedness on Cross-Lingual Transfer in Large Multilingual Automatic Speech Recognition, by Andrei Florian and 8 other authors</div>\n129\t    <a class=\"mobile-submission-download\" href=\"/pdf/2607.04814v1\">View PDF</a>\n130\t    <a class=\"mobile-submission-download\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/html/2607.04814v1\">HTML (experimental)</a>\n131\t\n132\t\n133\t\n134\t    <blockquote class=\"abstract mathjax\">\n135\t            <span class=\"descriptor\">Abstract:</span>Extending automatic speech recognition (ASR) to low-resource African languages is constrained by the prohibitive demands of data collection at scale. A promising direction is to leverage linguistic relatedness to enhance cross-lingual transfer from a related auxiliary language to the low-resource target by sequentially adapting on both. Although this strategy has shown meaningful improvements in small ASR models, its effectiveness in large ASR remains unclear. We extend this framework to large multilingual ASR through a systematic controlled experimental design spanning six factors, two Africa-centric corpora, and four large ASR models, isolating whether linguistic relatedness reliably predicts cross-lingual transfer gains in this setting. Across all conditions, pre-adaptation on related auxiliary languages yields no practically meaningful transfer improvements given minimal target-language data, suggesting that linguistic relatedness alone may not reliably predict cross-lingual transfer gains in large multilingual ASR, or constitute an effective strategy for extending such models to low-resource languages.\n136\t    </blockquote>\n137\t\n138\t    <!--CONTEXT-->\n139\t    <div class=\"metatable\">\n140\t      <table summary=\"Additional metadata\"><tr>\n141\t          <td class=\"tablecell label\">Subjects:</td>\n142\t          <td class=\"tablecell subjects\">\n143\t            <span class=\"primary-subject\">Computation and Language (cs.CL)</span>; Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI)</td>\n144\t        </tr><tr>\n145\t          <td class=\"tablecell label\">Cite as:</td>\n146\t          <td class=\"t